               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t16890516-55-off248-c153" targOrder="Y" targets="t16890516-55-defend239 t16890516-55-off248 t16890516-55-verdict250"></join>
         
               <p>
            
               
                  <persName id="t16890516-55-defend239" type="defendantName">
                     Christopher 
                     Ashley
                  <interp inst="t16890516-55-defend239" type="surname" value="Ashley"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16890516-55-defend239" type="given" value="Christopher"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16890516-55-defend239" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was Indicted for <rs id="t16890516-55-off248" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16890516-55-off248" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16890516-55-off248" type="offenceSubcategory" value="animalTheft"></interp>
               stealing a brown Gelding price 10 l.
            </rs> from one 
               
                  <persName id="t16890516-55-victim241" type="victimName">
                     Thomas 
                     Whittear
                  <interp inst="t16890516-55-victim241" type="surname" value="Whittear"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16890516-55-victim241" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16890516-55-victim241" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t16890516-55-off248 t16890516-55-victim241"></join>
                  </persName>
               
             of Tosseter in Northamptonshire, on the <rs id="t16890516-55-cd249" type="crimeDate">30th day of October</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t16890516-55-off248 t16890516-55-cd249"></join> last. The Evidence swore that the Prisoner had confessed it whilest he was in the Poultry Compter, and that he took away the Horse instead of his own; the Horse was brought to the Castle-Inn in Woodstreet, as was evidenced by the Ostler, and that the Owner of the Horse had his Horse again. The Prisoner was likewise charged with a Tankard that he stole at Tosseter, and had no Evidence on his side. So being an old Offender, he was found <rs id="t16890516-55-verdict250" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16890516-55-verdict250" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               Guilty
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t16890516-55-punish251" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16890516-55-punish251" type="punishmentCategory" value="noPunish"></interp>
